      "writtenOn": "2021-02-12T19:22:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "currently in the trace you see \"shader_compile\" and if it isn\u0027t caches then \"cache_miss\" as the child trace that dominates the time.  I\u0027m hoping whatever we add makes sense in the context of \"cache_miss\".  \n\nDoes this particular trace add more granularity than what we can infer from \"cache_miss\"?  Seeing how much time is spent in the GL driver is something I think we would like to see all the time.  However, the details of what skia method you are in should be reserved for  ATRACE_ANDROID_FRAMEWORK() tracing.\n\nIf this is the part that sends the GLSL to the driver compiler then something like \"compile_gl_program\" would be more descriptive.",
