      "writtenOn": "2021-02-12T21:48:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Does this particular trace add more granularity than what we can infer from \"cache_miss\"?\n\nYes. I have only looked at one trace (with a few cache_misses), but it tends to be a much shorter time.\n\n\u003e  Seeing how much time is spent in the GL driver is something I think we would like to see all the time.\n\nSounds good to me. Brian, does the amount of time spent in the GL driver map well to this method?\n\n\u003e However, the details of what skia method you are in should be reserved for  ATRACE_ANDROID_FRAMEWORK() tracing.\n\nAck.\n\n\u003e \n\u003e If this is the part that sends the GLSL to the driver compiler then something like \"compile_gl_program\" would be more descriptive.\n\nIt looks like compilation is on line 74, if we want to focus on just that piece.\n\nWhat I find interesting from looking at a trace (attached to https://buganizer.corp.google.com/issues/179848728#comment16), it looks like there\u0027s a substantial (relative to cache_miss) amount of time spent in between Compiler::toGLSL and this method. Should we be tracking anything there? (Admittedly, these shader_compiles still are only taking 16 ms at the most.)",
      "parentUuid": "319703f5_c174e406",
      "revId": "04951fcf0294d1b34c562fe41a129338be4e6a1d",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
