      "writtenOn": "2021-02-12T22:04:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For a typical draw, there will be three major chunks of time in the driver. Two calls to this function (which is essentially all driver work compiling each of the two shaders - vertex and fragment). Then a call to LinkProgram (which you have instrumented elsewhere). From previous tracing for flutter, I\u0027ve seen the work split up among those locations differently depending on gpu vendor, etc...\n\nThis function could certainly be summarized as \"driver_compile_shader\", and then call the other one \"driver_link_program\". (A program is ~two shaders).",
      "parentUuid": "be671c37_029c4973",
      "revId": "04951fcf0294d1b34c562fe41a129338be4e6a1d",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
