      "writtenOn": "2021-02-12T21:48:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Generally I\u0027m trying to make shader_compile more useful. From Brian:\n\n\"It might be interesting to put a trace inside the if (checkCompiled) { ... } scope of that function, too. It should be fast, but chrome skips that (for example) because of cross-process latency to read-back the result. (Shouldn\u0027t be an issue on Android...).\"\n\nI changed these to ALWAYS because the bug has an attached trace where they wanted more information. If we had had these in place already, that trace would\u0027ve contained the info that we think we might want. If I could reproduce the issue locally, I would turn on Skia tracing and get the extra information. Since I couldn\u0027t, I thought it would be more useful for us to get traces  that had the extra info. (Maybe another answer is that if this case is not reproducible then we shouldn\u0027t worry too much about it?)\n\nThe downsides to making it ALWAYS are (1) potential noise with more events and (2) slight performance impact (?). (Anything else I\u0027ve missed?)\n\nLet me know your preference.",
      "parentUuid": "e77c669c_a79fd0e0",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 79,
        "startChar": 8,
